```

This workflow provides a fully automated, repeatable, and reliable software delivery process, reducing manual effort and minimizing deployment risks.

# 42. Best Practices Implemented

This project follows several DevOps and software engineering best practices to ensure the deployment process is reliable, repeatable, and maintainable.

## Source Code Management

- Source code is maintained in GitHub.
- The pipeline is automatically triggered when changes are pushed to the **main** branch.
- Infrastructure configuration is stored as code using Azure DevOps YAML.

---

## Build Automation

The application is automatically built using Azure DevOps without requiring manual intervention.

The build process includes:

- Source code checkout
- Dependency restoration
- Solution compilation
- Unit testing
- Application publishing

Automating these tasks ensures every build is created using the same process.

---

## Automated Testing

Unit tests are executed before deployment.

Benefits include:

- Early defect detection
- Improved application quality
- Reduced production failures
- Increased confidence during deployments

Deployments proceed only if all tests complete successfully.

---

## Artifact-Based Deployment

Instead of deploying directly from source code, the pipeline creates a deployment artifact.

Advantages include:

- Same artifact is used across environments
- Faster deployments
- Build once, deploy many times
- Easy rollback
- Improved traceability

---

## Automated Deployment

Deployment to AWS EC2 is fully automated.

The deployment process includes:

- Artifact transfer
- Backup creation
- Application deployment
- Service restart
- Health verification

This removes manual deployment activities and reduces deployment errors.

---

## Deployment Backup

Before deploying a new version, the existing application is backed up.

Benefits:

- Rollback capability
- Reduced deployment risk
- Recovery from failed deployments

---

## Linux Service Management

The application is managed using systemd.

Advantages:

- Automatic restart
- Automatic startup after reboot
- Centralized logging
- Service monitoring
- Standard Linux administration

---

## Health Verification

A health check is executed after deployment.

Only if the application responds successfully is the deployment considered successful.

This prevents unhealthy deployments from being marked as completed.

---

## Secure Deployment

Deployment is performed using Azure DevOps SSH Service Connection.

Benefits:

- Encrypted communication
- No passwords stored in source code
- Secure authentication
- Centralized credential management

---

## Configuration Management

Pipeline configuration values are stored in Azure DevOps Variable Groups.

Advantages:

- Centralized configuration
- Easy updates
- Reusability
- Better security

